OL,4,Ccat banned from Costa cafe
OL,6,F"Recently, however, a fellow customer
OL,7,Fcomplained about Dillon's presence,
OL,8,Fresulting in Dillon being forced to
OL,9,Fstay outside. This has deeply affected
OL,10,Four community, transforming our
OL,11,Ftreasured coffee visits into
OL,12,Fmelancholic reminders of Dillon's
OL,13,Fabsence."
OL,15,FShe continued: "The petition is a call
OL,16,Ffor Costa to rethink its decision, to
OL,17,Ftake into account the mental health of
OL,18,Fits regulars and the happiness of
OL,19,FDillon who, like a loyal customer,
OL,20,Fenjoys the warmth of the indoors.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
